<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>EastEnders has released its nail-biting new comeback trailer and Mick Carter's son Ollie looks to be in danger. </p>

<p>The tot can be seen playing football in a new clip from the series as a mysterious woman takes pictures of him from the distance. </p>

<p>Mick (Danny Dyer), who plays with his son, is completely oblivious to the unknown woman who appears to be stalking him and Ollie.</p>

<p>Tension: EastEnders has released its nail-biting new comeback trailer and Mick Carter's son Ollie looks to be in danger</p>

<p>Elsewhere, Stacey Slater's (Lacey Turner) return to Walford appears to have not been well received by her ex best friend Ruby Allen (Louisa Lytton) as she asks Ruby why she doesn't look happy to see her.</p>

<p>Viewers are already aware that Stacey's husband Martin (James Bye) has moved on with Ruby during the Covid-19 lockdown.</p>

<p>Meanwhile, tensions are reaching breaking point between Chantelle Atkins (Jessica Plummer) and her evil husband Gray Atkins (Toby-Alexander Smith).</p>

<p>In the new trailer, he is seen confronting her when she arrives home and asks: 'Where are you, I've been trying you for the last 20 minutes' as she looked terrified.</p>

<p>She's back: Elsewhere, Stacey Slater's (Lacey Turner) return to Walford appears to have not been well received by her ex best friend Ruby Allen (Louisa Lytton)</p>

<p>Stalker: The tot can be seen playing football in a new clip from the series as a mysterious woman takes pictures of him from the distance</p>

<p>Torture: Tensions are reaching breaking point between Chantelle Atkins (Jessica Plummer) and her evil husband Gray Atkins (Toby-Alexander Smith)</p>

<p>Later, Chantelle can be seen apparently on the verge of tears as she sits in a bath and begs him not to do something to her. </p>

<p>Spoilers have previously revealed that Chantelle soon realises she finally needs to get away from Gray after months of torture during lockdown. </p>

<p>Soap fans will soon see her organise to meet with one of her husband's rival law firms to find a hard-nosed divorce lawyer. </p>

<p>Marriage from hell: Gray is seen confronting her when she arrives home and asks: 'Where are you, I've been trying you for the last 20 minutes' as she looked terrified</p>

<p>Drama: Viewers are already aware that Stacey's husband Martin has moved on with Ruby during the Covid-19 lockdown</p>

<p>When she realises how costly her legal fees will be, she meets with Kheerat for advice and the pair end up sharing a moment.</p>

<p>Later, she forms a plan to finally escape from Gray's clutches with the children while he is at work.</p>

<p>Elsewhere in the trailer, Sharon Mitchell (Letitia Dean) looks set to discover something unsettling as she is seen on the verge of tears. </p>

<p>EastEnders continues Mondays at 8pm and Tuesdays at 7.30pm on BBC One.</p>

